      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_015_0831_x__task_001/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "HiC-Pro is organized into four distinct modules following the main steps of Hi-C data analysis: (i) read alignment, (ii) detection and filtering of valid interaction products, (iii) binning and (iv) contact map normalization",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the read alignment stage as a core module of HiC-Pro using bowtie2.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-015-0831-x",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the bowtie2-based read alignment stage of the HiC-Pro pipeline",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:08.924861+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_015_0831_x__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's research question focuses narrowly on post-processing of SAM/BAM files, but the paper's scope is broader: HiC-Pro is a complete pipeline from raw reads to normalized contact maps, with alignment being only the first of four modules.",
        "The expected output 'config-system.txt' appears to be a specific implementation detail not documented in the paper passages provided.",
        "MultiQC is a third-party quality control tool not integrated into HiC-Pro; the paper describes HiC-Pro's own internal quality control mechanisms."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:08.924861+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_015_0831_x__task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes SAM/BAM processing and filtering of aligned reads (passages 5-6), but the task card title claims to 'reconstruct' this stage, which is not a stated research objective. The paper presents HiC-Pro as an existing pipeline that performs these steps, not a reconstruction task. Title does not align with the research_question or expected_outputs.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-015-0831-x",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the SAM processing stage that filters and sorts aligned Hi-C reads",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:25.877627+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_015_0831_x__task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "HiC-Pro proposes a fast sparse-based implementation of the iterative correction method [17], allowing normalization of genome-wide high-resolution contact matrices in a short time and with reasonable memory requirements.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper extensively discusses iterative correction (ICE) algorithm and its implementation. Passage 5 explicitly compares HiC-Pro's implementation with the iced package: 'The code for the normalization is available as a standalone package (https://github.com/hiclib/iced) as well as being included in HiC-Pro.'",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-015-0831-x",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the ICE normalization algorithm iteratively correct and balance raw Hi-C contact matrices using the iced Python module?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:25.877627+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_015_0831_x__task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The code for the normalization is available as a standalone package (https://github.com/hiclib/iced) as well as being included in HiC-Pro.",
      "asbval:note": "iced is confirmed as a standalone Python package for iterative correction normalization.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-015-0831-x",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
