      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Python (>2.7) with the pysam, bx.python, numpy and scipy libraries",
      "asbval:note": "Paper lists required Python libraries (pysam, bx.python, numpy, scipy) but does NOT specify version pinning constraints (\u22651.18.1, \u22651.4.1, \u22650.15.4, \u22650.8.8). The card claims specific minimum versions that are not present in the paper. Paper only states 'Python (>2.7)' without version constraints on dependencies.",
